FORECAST - Danish KFK lowers 97 expectations . Leading Danish grain and feedstuffs wholesaler A / S Korn og Foderstof Kompagniet ( KFK ) downgraded on Tuesday its full - year expectations to the level of 1996 results . In February , KFK posted a disappointing 1996 net profit of 75 million crowns , dramatically lower than the previous year ' s 191 million crowns but foresaw " a somewhat better " 1997 result . The firm said that 1997 ' s first quarter did not meet expectations , with higher raw material prices and late spring sewing meaning delayed seed and fertiliser sales . - - Chris Follett , Copenhagen newsroom + 45 - 33969652 
